                    <div class="row sync-description-label">
                    Sirv automatically copies product images to your Sirv account upon first request. <a href="https://sirv.com/help/articles/magento-cdn-sirv-extension/#sync" target="_blank" class="sirv-open-in-new-window">Learn more</a>.<br/><br/>
                    It is also possible to pre-sync images via the "Sync Media Gallery" button below.
                    </div>
                ]]></notice>
                <value></value>
            </field>
            <field>
                <name>media_storage_info</name>
                <label>Media gallery size</label>
                <type>button</type>
                <type_class>\Sirv\Magento2\Block\Adminhtml\Settings\Edit\Form\Element\Button\MediaStorageInfo</type_class>
                <value>Calculate</value>
                <notice><![CDATA[Estimate how much storage space you require on Sirv.]]></notice>
            </field>
            <field>
                <name>delete_cached_images</name>
                <label>Delete cached images during sync</label>
                <type>radios</type>
                <type_class>\Sirv\Magento2\Block\Adminhtml\Settings\Edit\Form\Element\Radios\Switcher</type_class>
                <options>
                    <option>
                        <label>Yes</label>
                        <value>true</value>
                    </option>
                    <option>
                        <label>No</label>
                        <value>false</value>
                    </option>
                </options>
                <tooltip><![CDATA[
                    Save disk space by deleting the many resized images generated by the Magento product image cache. Sirv does not require them.
                    <br/><br/>
                    If required, you can regenerate the Magento image cache with the Magento CLI command: <b>php bin/magento catalog:images:resize</b>
                ]]></tooltip>
                <notice><![CDATA[
                    <div class="cached_images_notice" data-mage-init='{"sirvCatalogImagesCacheData": {"ajaxUrl": "{{CATALOG_IMAGES_CACHE_INFO_URL}}", "flushUrl": "{{FLUSH_URL}}", "cacheInfo": {"count": {{COUNT}}, "countLabel": "{{COUNT_LABEL}}", "timestamp": {{TIMESTAMP}}}} }'>

                    <div class="catalog-images-cache-data-spinner spinner hidden"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></div><span class="catalog-images-cache-data-progress hidden"> Calculating cache size... <span class="catalog-images-cache-data-progress-counter" data-count="0">0</span>%</span>

                    <div class="catalog-images-cache-data">

                    Your Magento cache contains <span class="catalog-images-cache-info-count">{{COUNT_LABEL}} resized image{{SUFFIX}} on {{DATE}}</span>.

                    <a href="#"
                        onclick="return false"
                        class="catalog-images-cache-info-recalculate-link"
                        title="Count the number of images in the cache"
                        >Recalculate.</a>

                    <br/>
                    <span class="catalog-images-cache-flush">
                    <a href="#"
                        onclick="return false"
                        class="catalog-images-cache-flush-link"
                        title="Delete pregenerated product images files"
                        >Delete cache...</a>
                    </span>

                    </div>

                    </div>
                ]]></notice>
                <value>false</value>
            </field>
            <field>
                <name>synchronizer</name>
                <label>Sync status</label>
                <type>synchronizer</type>
                <type_class>\Sirv\Magento2\Block\Adminhtml\Settings\Edit\Form\Element\Synchronizer</type_class>
            </field>
            <field>
                <name>alt_text</name>
                <label>Copy alt text to Sirv</label>
